name: Southwestern Grilled Chicken Wraps
author: Shara Bailey
summary: Grilled chicken wraps with a lil' kick.
ingredients: 4 medium skinless, boneless chicken breast halves
1 (15.25 ounce) can whole kernel corn, drained
1 (15 ounce) can black beans, rinsed and drained
2 tablespoons ranch dressing, or to taste
directions: Preheat an outdoor grill for medium heat and lightly oil the grate
Cook on the preheated grill until chicken is no longer pink in the center and the juices run clear, 5 to 7 minutes per side
An instant-read thermometer inserted into the center should read at least 165 degrees F (74 degrees C)
Allow to cool enough to handle, about 10 minutes; slice into bite-size pieces
Combine corn, beans, lettuce, tomato, green onions, Cheddar cheese, and ranch dressing in a bowl; stir in chicken
Assemble wraps as desired in tortillas
